						<summary>

						<p>Fragments of a slab lying in the temple of Yāgaṇṭīśvara.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to the 16th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It refer to gifts of land made to certain artisans such as masons, cartmen etc., who served in the construction of the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
